stylometry: Decision trees are important in problem solving becuase they provide us with probabilities in decision making. A decision tree is set up with a "Yes" and "No" concept. If a company were to decide yes on producing the product, the "yes" decision trees would show all the factors, and outcomes to producting that product. The "No" decision would show nothing because if the company chose to do not to produce the product then the outcome would be that no costs were incurred no profits were made. Lets say we own a house, a condo, and apartment. We know the costs of having these three properities and we now want to lease them out. From there we create three decision variables. Yes or No to lease the house, condo, and apartment. There we put in the factors of leasing the these three properties. The profits of leasing these three properties and the costs or leasing these three and in the end the probability would show whether or not if leasing the properties would cover the cost of owning it. We obviously would do this will all three properties and we then can decide whether leasing these properties would be a good idea or not.
